    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Flooring</title>
        <para>The school bus flooring may vary in color and material type per the requirements of the school district.
            The center isle is a raised surface type tread to eliminate possible slipping in the walkway area. The
            entrance area and step well are also a tread style flooring. The wheel well covers are a black composite
            molded material (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f4700458">Fig. 58, Item 2</hotlnk>) with the heater hoses enclosed in the outer section (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f4700458">Fig. 58 Item 3</hotlnk>) of the wheel well against the bus wall.
        </para>
        <figure id="f4700458" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/g4700458.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 58. Wheel Well Cover</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. CHAIR MOUNTING RAIL</callout1>
                <callout1>2. WHEEL WELL COVER</callout1>
                <callout1>3. MOLDED HEATER HOSE COVER INTEGRAL WITH WHEEL WELL COVER</callout1>
                <callout1>4. HEATER HOSE COVER ALONG BUS WALL</callout1>
                <callout1>5. BUS FLOOR COVERING</callout1>
                <callout1>6. WHEEL WELL COVER MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcsubproc>
